Epilogue page skeleton (Constitution III.13 / Amendment W).

One of the six terminal-outcome pages (spec-116 FR-116-4.2). Deliberately
narrative, unlike the county dossier's stat-scaffold: the headline and body
below are deterministic, dev-authored copy, not narrator-generated prose —
so this page carries no {narrative} fence (III.6's model-pin/cache-key
discipline governs AI-attributed blocks, and none of this text is
AI-attributed). Headline and body are always present for any recognized
outcome key; an unrecognized key is refused before this template ever runs
(babylon.projection.vault.render_epilogue.render_epilogue raises loud, per
III.11, rather than this template ever needing an absence block — a page
that structurally cannot be incomplete has none to render).
-#}
